I"¨<p>A macro like</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>#if xyz
...
#endf
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>might be represented as<br />
<img src="/assets/if-box-if.png" alt="ifdiagram" /></p>

<p>instead of as ASCII Art</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>#if xyz {
...
}
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="better-yet">Better Yet</h2>

<p><img src="/assets/if-box-if2.png" alt="ifdiagram" /></p>

<h2 id="das">DaS</h2>

<p>Diagrams As Syntax</p>

<p>Not a full-blown VPL, just</p>
<ul>
  <li>rects</li>
  <li>ellipses</li>
  <li>text</li>
  <li>lines.</li>
</ul>

<p>SVG already supports the above.</p>

<p>ASCII was supported by mid-1900s hardware.</p>

<p>SVG is supported by 2000s hardware.</p>

